---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Can Ocek Portfolio"
  description="Draft portfolio foundation for Can Ocek across technology, strategy, and music."
>
  <section class="hero container" aria-labelledby="home-title">
    <div class="hero__content">
      <p class="eyebrow">Portfolio foundation</p>
      <h1 id="home-title">Can &Ouml;cek</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="hero__support">
      <!-- TODO: Replace with final personal positioning copy. -->
      <p class="lede">
        I build systems, shape ideas, and make projects work across technology, strategy, and music.
      </p>
      <p>
        This first version is intentionally small: a static structure for selected work, music,
        background, CV content, and contact details as they are verified for publication.
      </p>
      <div class="button-row" aria-label="Primary actions">
        <a class="button primary" href="/work/">View work</a>
        <a class="button" href="/music/">Music</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="featured-title">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">First focus</p>
      <h2 id="featured-title">Three areas to build around</h2>
      <div class="grid three section-offset">
        <article class="panel">
          <p class="panel__meta">Systems</p>
          <h3>Web intelligence and retrieval</h3>
          <p>
            A technical case-study area for data collection, structured storage, and retrieval
            work once project details are verified.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="panel">
          <p class="panel__meta">Sound</p>
          <h3>Music performance and production</h3>
          <p>
            A central creative section for guitar, vocals, arrangement, recording, production,
            live audio, and related media work.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="panel">
          <p class="panel__meta">Strategy</p>
          <h3>Business and platform design</h3>
          <p>
            A place for technical-business work such as CRM modeling, process design, and
            cross-disciplinary project execution.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="disciplines-title">
    <div class="container two-column">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Method</p>
        <h2 id="disciplines-title">Working across disciplines</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid">
        <p class="lede">
          The common thread is not a list of tools. It is the habit of understanding the system,
          finding the missing pieces, and doing the work needed to connect them.
        </p>
        <p>
          The next implementation sprints will turn this foundation into navigable project drafts
          without pretending that unfinished source material is final.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
